>> source: https://www.bbcgoodfood.com/recipes/tofu-asparagus-pad-thai
>> time required: 30 minutes
>> image: https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/30/2020/08/recipe-image-legacy-id-605574_11-c9528db.jpg?resize=768,574

Cook the @noodles{200%g} following pack instructions. Mix the lime juice, @tamarind{1%tbsp} and @chilli sauce{2%tbsp} in a small bowl. Set aside.

Heat 1 tbsp @oil{2%tbsp} in a non-stick frying pan or wok and fry the @tofu{300%g} for ~{5-8%min}s until golden all over. Set aside.

Add the remaining oil and stir-fry the @asparagus{10} until tender. Tip in the @spring onions{6}, @beansprouts{300%g} and @garlic{3%clove}. Cook for ~{2%min}s more. Stir in the drained noodles, sauce and some salt. Mix in the tofu and heat through. Serve with @coriander{0%handful}, salted peanuts and lime wedges.
